msgid ""
"The \"Balancing Algorithm\" field is important to care about as many web "
"applications depend on a state. For example, if your web application "
"stores session data on a local disk, you may get some trouble when using "
"an algorithm like Round Robin. In such a case, the request of the same "
"client always needs to be sent to the same backend servers. For example "
"by default PHP stores session data in files while Ruby on Rails stores "
"session information in a cookie by default. Please look up your web "
"framework documentation for information how this is handled. Consider "
"writeing files as problematic as well if there is no shared storage."
