#: ../../source/manual/how-tos/haproxy.rst:146
msgid ""
"Now its nearly done. The only thing that needs to be configured for "
"HAProxy is a Public Service. A Public Service is a a group of bound ports"
" which are used for incoming connections. From this Public Service we "
"need to know which backend the request will routed to. For this, the "
"previously configured action is needed. If you got multiple domains with "
"the same port on one IP, you differentiate them with rules! Don't create "
"multiple Public Services. For example, if you only want to forward "
"example.org:80 and example.com:80, just create one Public Service. If you"
" want to forward example.org:80, example.org:443, example.com:80, and "
"example.com:443, create only two Public Services, one for port 80 "
"(example.org and example.com) and one for port 443 (example.org and "
"example.com)."
msgstr ""

